'''''Young Jedi Knights: Lightsabers''''' is a [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]] young-adult novel written by [[Kevin J. Anderson]] and [[Rebecca Moesta]]. It is the fourth book in the ''[[Star Wars: Young Jedi Knights]]'' series, and it was first published by [[Berkley Boulevard]] in [[March]] [[1996]].

The novel was reprinted in ''[[Young Jedi Knights: The Rise of the Shadow Academy]]'' (1996) and ''[[Young Jedi Knights: Jedi Sunrise]]'' ([[2003]]).

==Publisher's summary==
''Luke Skywalker has come to a grim conclusion. With the threat of a new generation of Dark Jedi being trained at the Shadow Academy, he knows the New Republic will need all the fighters it can muster. At last, it is time for the young Jedi Knights to build their lightsabers.''

''But there is more to mastering the ancient weapon than mere swordsmanship. Each student must learn about the mysterious bond between Jedi and lightsaber. For Jacen and Jaina, success will mean growing stronger in the Force. But for one of their friends, failure will mean tragedy...''

==Plot summary==
With the growing threat of the [[Second Imperium]] and the [[Dark Jedi/Legends|Dark Jedi]] being trained at the [[Shadow Academy]], [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke]] decides, against his better judgment, to accelerate the training of his [[Jedi Praxeum|Jedi academy]] students, and asks them to build and start using their own [[Lightsaber/Legends|lightsabers]]. Unfortunately, [[Tenel Ka Djo|Tenel Ka]] has hastily constructed an inferior weapon. The young [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knights]] proudly rise to the challenge, but tragedy strikes when during a sparring session with [[Darth Caedus|Jacen Solo]], Tenel's blade dissipates, causing Jacen to accidentally sever her left arm just above the elbow. Jacen is horrified that he has maimed his friend. Tenel is spirited back to her homeworld of [[Hapes/Legends|Hapes]] to recover.

On Hapes,Tenel Ka is watched over by her [[Parent/Legends|grandmother]], [[Ta'a Chume]], who is determined to keep her safe amid court intrigue and [[Death/Legends|assassinations]] attempts by a treacherous [[Ambassador/Legends|ambassador]]. She is once again exposed to the old [[Gender/Legends|woman]]'s schemings, as she tries to initiate her to [[Hapan]] [[Politics/Legends|politics]], and persuade her to renounce her [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] training. Jacen, [[Jaina Solo Fel|Jaina]] and [[Lowbacca]] arrive later in a welcome respite, but this does not last; after an unknown [[Assassin/Legends|assassin]] detonates a [[Bomb/Legends|bomb]] in the [[Fountain Palace|royal palace]], Ta'a Chume determines that their lives are all in danger, and she and the Jedi trainees retire to an isolated island in the middle of the Hapan [[Water/Legends|ocean]].

Even there, however, they are not safe; they barely escape another assassination attempt from a group of [[Bartokk]] killers. Upon their return to the mainland, the [[Queen Mother]] orders Ambassador [[Yfra]], who was responsible for the attacks, arrested. After the ambassador is exposed and arrested, Tenel Ka has determined that she wishes to continue her training, and returns to [[Yavin 4/Legends|Yavin 4]] with her friends, and constructs a new lightsaber. Meanwhile, [[Zekk]] trains under [[Tamith Kai]], becoming one of the top students at the [[Shadow Academy]]. The Shadow Academy is devoted to rebuilding the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Empire]] to power under its leader, the inexplicably alive [[Emperor/Legends|Emperor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]]. To prove his skills, Zekk engages the other top student, [[Vilas]], in a [[Lightsaber duel/Legends|lightsaber duel]] and kills him. 

==Continuity==
The book mentioned that [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] didn't face [[Brakiss]] since he left [[Jedi Praxeum|Jedi academy]]. Yet in [[17 ABY/Legends|17 ABY]] in ''[[The New Rebellion]]'' novel during [[Almanian Uprising]] Luke [[Duel on Telti|dueled]] Brakiss on [[Telti/Legends|Telti]]. [[Augwynne Djo]] is mistakenly listed as the [[Parent/Legends|mother]] of [[Teneniel Djo]] and continues this by saying that she is the grandmother of Tenel Ka, instead as grandmother and great-grandmother respectively.

